sis of the Moral Foundations in Ayn Rand <ref>{{cite news |title=So Who's The Guy Who Just Beat Eric Cantor? Meet Dave Brat|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/06/10/dave-brat-eric-cantor_n_5482610.html|publisher=[[The Huffington Post]] |accessdate=June 11, 2014}}</ref>\n* {{cite journal |last=Park |first=Walter G |last2=Brat |first2= David A |title=Cross-Country R&D and Growth: Variations on a Theme of Mankiw-Romer-Weil |journal=Eastern Economic Journal |date=Summer 1996 |volume=22 |issue=3 |pages=345\u201354 |url=http://nw08.american.edu/~wgp/park_eej.pdf |accessdate=June 13, 2014}}\n* {{cite web |title=American Underdog: Proof That Principles Matter |url=https://www.amazon.com/American-Underdog-Proof-Principles-Matter/dp/1455539910 |publisher=Center Street |accessdate=June 27, 2016}} (2016)<ref name=\"Takala Examiner Story\">{{cite news|first=Rudy|last=Takala|authorlink=Rudy Takala|title=Dave Brat to release his first book this week|url=http://www.washingtonexaminer.com/dave-brat-to-release-his-first-book-this-week/article/2594977|publisher=[[The Washington Examiner]] |accessdate=June 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBrat was raised in a [[Presbyterian]] church and his wife, Laura, is a [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]].<ref name=\"themorningsun1\"/> Splitting their time between two churches,<ref name=\"themorningsun1\"/> they are parishioners of [[St. Mary's Catholic School (Richmond, Virginia)|St. Mary Catholic Church]] in [[Richmond, Virginia|Richmond]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://davebratforcongress.com/about-dave/ |title=David Brat campaign website |publisher=Davebratforcongress.com |date= |accessdate=June 11, 2014}}</ref> Brat also identifies himself as a [[Calvinism|Calvinist]] and lists affiliations with Christ Episcopal Church, Third Presbyterian, and Shady Grove Methodist.<ref name=TimesBiblicalViews>{{cite news|last=Dias|first=Elizabeth|date=June 11, 2014|title=David Brat's Biblical Views Shape His Tea Party Politics|url=http://time.com/2860967/david-brats-biblical-views-shape-his-tea-party-politics|work=Time|accessdate=June 12, 2014}}</ref>\n\nBrat moved to Virginia in 1996 with his wife, Laura.<ref>{{cite news|author=|url=http://dailyentertainmentnews.com/breaking-news/laura-brat-virginias-7th-congressional-district-politician-dave-brats-wife|title=Laura Brat profile|publisher=Dailyentertainmentnews.com|date=January 15, 1962|accessdate=June 12, 2014}}</ref> They live in [[Glen Allen, Virginia|Glen Allen]], a suburb of Richmond.<ref>{{cite news|title=A look at Eric Cantor, tea party challenger|url=http://www.lasvegassun.com/news/2014/jun/06/a-look-at-eric-cantor-tea-party-challenger|publisher=Las Vegas Sun|accessdate=June 17, 2014}}</ref> They have two children.<ref>{{cite web|title=About Dave Brat|url=http://davebrat.com/about-dave|website=davebrat.com|publisher=Friends for Dave Bray|accessdate=September 26, 2014}}</ref>\n\nBrat's brother Dan is a [[medical doctor]] specializing in neuropathology.  He is the chair of the Department of Pathology at Northwestern University. His youngest brother, Jim, is a [[Los Angeles]]-based real estate attorney.<ref name=\"themorningsun1\"/><ref>{{cite news |author=Mark Holmberg |date=June 11, 2014 |url=http://wtvr.com/2014/06/11/holmberg-where-does-the-dave-brat-toppling-of-eric-cantor-rank/ |title=Where does the Dave Brat toppling of Eric Cantor rank? |publisher=[[WTVR-TV]] |accessdate=June 12, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n* [https://brat.house.gov/ Congressman Dave Brat] official U.S. House site\n* [https://davebrat.com/ Dave Brat for Congress]\n* [http://faculty.rmc.edu/dbrat/ Professor David Brat at Randolph-Macon College]{{dead link|date=July 2018}}\n* {{DMOZ|Regional/North_America/United_States/Virginia/Government/Federal/US_House_of_Representatives/Dave_Brat_%5BR-7%5D}}\n* {{C-SPAN|davidbrat}}\n* {{CongLinks | congbio=B001290 | votesmart=152270 | fec=H4VA07143 | congress=dave-brat/B001290 }}<!--\nLinks 